file=Brand Studio/tempo/operational/skill/tempo-skill-routing.md · h=name: tempo-skill-routing\ntype: operational/skill\nstatus: consolidated from the "Boundaries" sections of tempo's skill files — no new logic invented\nassigned_agent: tempo (Brand Studio / Audio Branding)\ndate_added: 2026-07-08\n · p:=Tempo's routing map. Triggers: `operational/commands/tempo-commands.md`.\n · wif:Where Identity Fits=Tempo has no identity — spark holds Brand Studio's. Universal-only principles.\n · tp:The Pair=```\nusage-licensing   (RIGHTS — verify against the actual use, register, sweep expiries; · tb=\|            ambiguity → operator/counsel, quoted) · tp:The Pair=v\nsound-identity    (FIT — the sonic guide per brand, derived from the other definers;\nselections registry-only; drift flagged)\n```\n\nRights gate fit: nothing is selectable until it's cleared. For brands doing no audio content, both are documented no-ops — structure intact, nothing runs.\n · hr:Handoff Rules=- **pixel/pulse → tempo**: any produced content carrying audio invokes the pair (selection + license ref travel with the manifest).\n- **License spend** → operator, board's gate at its thresholds. **Lapses** flag live uses → operator with options.\n- **spark**: audio coherence becomes a gate reference once a brand's sonic guide exists (dormant line until then, coherence-qa's pattern).\n- **Jurisdiction/counsel questions** → operator, always.\n · p:Precedence="Can we use this" → licensing. "What should this sound like" → sound-identity. Both run on any new audio content.\n · f:=No guide/registry → the build/acquisition loops run first; neutral-labeled or nothing ships in the meantime.\n